body:
After the fixes in #5529 and #5530, foreach support for associative arrays, queues, and dynamic arrays has been improved. However, when dealing with more complex structures, such as the following:
```
rand int queue_1d[$];
rand int queue[$][$];
rand int dyn[][]; 
rand int queue_dyn[$][];
rand int dyn_queue[][$];
rand int queue_unp[$][3];
rand int unp_queue[3][$];
```
There are still unexpected problems.

